hazmatsuit.Name: Spacesuit

The urgency of what would later be known as Project Nova required Cobalt to bypass the design phase of an EVA suit - something that would normally take years when they had weeks. Using early Soviet designs (acquired by costly industrial espionage), Cobalt managed to produce a limited number of protective space suits. The whereabouts of most of them are unknown, but some were retained for terrestrial applications, given their radiation protection properties.

sofa.pattern.Name: Sofa - Pattern
sofa.pattern.Description:
A beat up, used, stained, discarded sofa with a floral pattern. Still comfortable, though.

[color=#40c34b]Having this item in your Steam Inventory means you'll be able to craft it in game.[/color]

This item will be permanently bound to your steam account.

industrial.wall.light.Name: Industrial Lights
industrial.wall.light.Description:
Industrial lights to illuminate your base. can be placed on floors, ceilings, or walls. comes in Red, Green, and White variations.

[color=#40c34b]Having this item in your Steam Inventory means you'll be able to craft it in game.[/color]

This item will be permanently bound to your steam account.

attire.snowman.helmet.Name: Snowman Helmet
attire.snowman.helmet.Description:
A snowman helmet which provides ample protection.

[color=#40c34b]Having this item in your Steam Inventory means you'll be able to craft it in game. If you sell, trade or break this item you will no longer have this ability in game.[/color]

firework.boomer.pattern.Name: Pattern Boomer
firework.boomer.pattern.Description:
A special boomer which allows you light up the night sky with a custom pattern that you draw. Multiple colors and altitude settings are available.

[color=#40c34b]Having this item in your Steam Inventory means you'll be able to craft it in game.[/color]

This item will be permanently bound to your steam account.
